⚙️ Installation and Setup
1. Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/vaibhavibtech2023-dev/resume-analyzer.git
cd resume-analyzer
2. Create a virtual environment:
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate      (Windows)
source venv/bin/activate   (Mac/Linux)
3. Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
🔑 4. Add Hugging Face API Key

Create an environment variable:

HF_API_KEY=your_huggingface_token

👉 This is required for BERT semantic similarity.

5. Run the application:
python main.py
6. Open in browser:
http://127.0.0.1:5000
🚀 Usage
👨‍💼 Recruiter Mode:
Upload multiple resumes
Provide a job description
Get ranked candidates with scores, matched skills, and feedback
👩‍💻 Candidate Mode:
Upload a single resume
Provide a job description
Get ATS-style evaluation with strengths and improvement areas
🌐 Deployment

The application can be deployed on:

Render
Railway
PythonAnywhere

👉 Uses Gunicorn + Hugging Face API, making it lightweight and suitable for cloud deployment.

